<h2 id="optimization-strategies">Optimization Strategies</h2>

<p>Most HVAC contractors set up LSA and forget about it. Active optimization increases lead quality and reduces costs over time.</p>

<h3>Review Management</h3>

<p>Customer reviews directly impact ad visibility and lead costs. HVAC contractors with 4.5+ star ratings get 60% more leads at 25% lower cost per lead compared to companies with 3.5-4.0 star ratings.</p>

<p>Review optimization tactics:</p>
<ul>
<li>Send review requests within 24 hours of job completion</li>
<li>Follow up with satisfied customers after 1 week if they haven't left a review</li>
<li>Respond to all reviews, especially negative ones, professionally</li>
<li>Use a systematic review collection process through your CRM</li>
</ul>

<h3>Response Time Optimization</h3>

<p>Google measures how quickly you respond to LSA leads. Contractors who respond within 5 minutes get 3x more leads than those who take 30+ minutes to respond. Set up immediate notifications and have a system for rapid response during business hours.</p>

<h3>Lead Quality Scoring</h3>

<p>Not all LSA leads are equal. Track lead sources and identify patterns in high-quality leads. Adjust your service offerings and target areas based on which generate the best customers.</p>

<p>Quality indicators to track:</p>
<ul>
<li>Job value per lead source</li>
<li>Conversion rate by service type</li>
<li>Customer lifetime value by acquisition channel</li>
<li>Payment collection rates</li>
</ul>

