<h2 id="common-mistakes-to-avoid">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

<p>These mistakes cost HVAC contractors thousands in wasted ad spend:</p>

<h3>Mistake 1: Setting Service Areas Too Large</h3>
<p>Casting too wide a net generates leads you can't serve profitably. A contractor in Dallas setting their service area to include Fort Worth (35 miles away) will get leads they either can't serve or must charge extra for travel time.</p>

<h3>Mistake 2: Ignoring Lead Quality Patterns</h3>
<p>If emergency repair leads convert at 40% but maintenance leads convert at 10%, allocate more budget to emergency services. Many contractors treat all leads equally instead of optimizing spend based on conversion data.</p>

<h3>Mistake 3: Poor Review Management</h3>
<p>One 1-star review can drop your ad visibility significantly. Respond to negative reviews professionally and implement systems to collect more positive reviews from satisfied customers.</p>

<h3>Mistake 4: Slow Response Times</h3>
<p>HVAC emergencies require immediate response. Contractors who take 30+ minutes to respond lose 70% of potential jobs to faster competitors. Set up instant SMS and email notifications for LSA leads.</p>

